{{Infobox school |name = Albena Lake-Hodge Comprehensive School |image = |alt = |caption = |established = 1953 |type = [[Secondary school]] |affiliation = [[Government of Anguilla]] |principal = Joyce Webster |colors = |uniform = |location = [[The Valley, Anguilla|The Valley]] |country = [[Anguilla]] | coordinates = {{Coord|18.2156295|-63.05032249999999|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = Anguilla }} '''Albena Lake-Hodge Comprehensive School''' ('''ALHCS''') is the sole government secondary school of [[Anguilla]], in [[The Valley, Anguilla|The Valley]]. {{Asof|2017}} it had about 1,062 students. It has two campuses, A and B. Forms 1-2 go to campus B while forms 3-6 go to Campus A.<ref name=schools>"[http://www.gov.ai/schools.php Schools]." Government of Anguilla. Retrieved on December 7, 2017.</ref> It is named after [[Albena Lake-Hodge]].
It opened as '''The Valley Secondary School''' on 21 September 1953. Its first principal, J. T. Thom, was from [[Guyana]]. It received its current name in 1986. It previously served only Anguilla's elite, but became a universal secondary school.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theanguillian.com/2014/06/celebrating-60-years-of-secondary-education-exhibition-now-open/|title=CELEBRATING 60 YEARS OF SECONDARY EDUCATION EXHIBITION NOW OPEN|publisher=''[[The Anguillan]]''|date=2014-06-27|accessdate=2017-12-07}}</ref>
In 2015 principal Ingrid Lake retired, so Joyce Webster became the principal.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theanguillian.com/2015/09/alhcs-principal-i-will-be-fair-firm-loving/|title=ALHCS PRINCIPAL: "I WILL BE FAIR, FIRM, LOVING"|publisher=''[[The Anguillan]]''|date=2015-09-14|accessdate=2017-12-07}}</ref>
By 2016 the Anguillan government was developing a master plan for the school's redevelopment.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theanguillian.com/2016/03/master-plan-to-redevelop-anguillas-comprehensive-school/|title=MASTER PLAN TO REDEVELOP ANGUILLA’S COMPREHENSIVE SCHOOL|publisher=''[[The Anguillan]]''|date=2016-03-29|accessdate=2017-12-07}}</ref>
There are 48 [[Caribbean Advanced Proficiency Examination]] (CAPE) units offered, as well as 32 [[Caribbean Secondary Examination Certificate]] (CSEC) courses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://theanguillian.com/2015/12/albena-lake-hodge-comprehensive-school-speech-night-2015/|title=ALBENA LAKE HODGE COMPREHENSIVE SCHOOL SPEECH NIGHT, 2015|publisher=''[[The Anguillan]]''|date=2015-12-14|accessdate=2017-12-07}}</ref>
