{{About|a recreational space|student organizational bodies in universities|Common room (university)}}
[[File:Common Room I.jpg|thumb|A [[Sixth form]] common room.]] [[File:Kesgrave Hall School (Boys Common Room) - geograph.org.uk - 473960.jpg|thumb|Boys Common Room at [[Kesgrave Hall School]], United Kingdom.]]
The phrase '''common room''' is used especially in British and Canadian English to describe a type of shared [[wiktionary:Lounge|lounge]], most often found in [[dormitory|dormitories]], at (for example) [[university|universities]], [[college]]s,<ref>{{cite web | url=http://scr.chch.ox.ac.uk/ | title=Senior Common Room | publisher=[[Christ Church, Oxford|Christ Church]], [[University of Oxford]], UK | accessdate=2 June 2011 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606070034/http://scr.chch.ox.ac.uk/ | archivedate=6 June 2011 | df= }}</ref> [[military base]]s, [[hospital]]s, [[rest home]]s, [[hostel]]s, and even minimum-security [[prison]]s.<ref name=book>{{cite book|last1=Davis|first1=Park|last2=Craig|first2=Susannah|title=The Complete Idiot's Guide to Running a Bed and Breakfast|date=2001|publisher=Penguin|pages=229-230|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=yIgWt_Lrrs8C&pg=PA229&lpg=PA229&dq=what+should+a+common+room+feature&source=bl&ots=bXOJQOZuJK&sig=lzxdekZoJ5RibX3o6T8MFIfpjYk&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjRvML01NbQAhUFOiYKHeo3CP4Q6AEITDAL#v=onepage&q=what%20should%20a%20common%20room%20feature&f=false|accessdate=2 December 2016}}</ref> It is generally connected to several private rooms, and may incorporate a [[bathroom]]. However, they may also be found in [[day school]]s and [[sixth form]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://pinnacle-furniture.co.uk/blog/a-guide-to-sixth-form-furniture/|title=A Guide to Sixth Form Furniture|publisher=Pinnacle Furniture|accessdate=2 December 2016}}</ref>
Regular features include [[couch]]es, [[television]]s, [[coffee table]]s, and other generic lounge [[furniture]] for socializing.<ref name=book /> Depending on its location and purpose of use, a common room may be known by another name. For instance, in [[mental hospital]]s, where access is usually restricted to the daytime hours, this type of room is often called a "day room".<ref name=book />
In Singapore, the term usually refers to a [[bedroom]] without attached bathroom in an [[Housing and Development Board|HDB]] apartment unit.<ref>{{cite web|title=Definitions of Common Room|url=http://www.propertyguru.com.sg/question/135872/what-is-indicated-by-a-common-room-actually-is-thi|website=Property Guru|accessdate=2 December 2016}}</ref>
Common rooms are mentioned in the [[Harry Potter]] series.
